{
  "id": "binary-star-orbit",
  "name": "Binary Star System - Gravitational Orbits",
  "description": "Two stars orbiting their common center of mass due to mutual gravitational attraction. Demonstrates Newton's Law of Universal Gravitation: F = Gm₁m₂/r². Both bodies orbit the barycenter at distances inversely proportional to their masses. Kepler's laws apply to both orbits.",
